main event: On April 14, 1950, multiple rectangular flying objects were observed in the sky over Fort Monmouth, New Jersey.
interesting points: The objects were observed in a formation moving erratically while maintaining an elevation of approximately 2,000 feet,Each object was rectangular, measuring about 34 feet long and 11 feet thick,The objects were amber in color and had flat surfaces with no visible means of propulsion,The sighting lasted for approximately 3-4 minutes before the objects disappeared,The witness noted the formation changed position and altitude smoothly without any visible strings or contrails.
witness description: A male individual driving on Wilson Ave, near Main St.
